<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Culture characteristics.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Cultures</emphasis>
initially are white, growing fast up to 8 cm in diam. after 3 days and entirely covering the 9 cm Petri dish after 4 days, becoming greenish-olivaceous after 7-10 days and grey olivaceous after 30 days. In reverse, the cultures are the same as the upper colour after 7 days, becoming olivaceous grey to iron grey after 30 days. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Colonies</emphasis>
are 
<normalizedToken originalValue="ﬂat">ﬂat</normalizedToken>
with a uniform texture; sterile.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Habitat and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
